div1.p:
WILLIAM HAZARD sworn. - I took a part of a spoon from the prisoner, and part I found in the privy; I took that with the crest upon it out of his pocket; this is the handle of a spoon: on the 3d of June, towards the evening, after I had been at the prosecutor's, about seven o'clock in the evening, I found it in the privy below at the George, in the Haymarket; the prisoner had been there that day about last an hour before I found it. (The spoons were sworn to by
Mary Baseman
).
